            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1387268267,
            "creation_date": 1387268267,
            "body": "<p>Maybe it's wisest to start with a clean slate: <a href=\"https://jersey.java.net/documentation/latest/getting-started.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://jersey.java.net/documentation/latest/getting-started.html<\/a> If Maven is not an option, create the Maven project anyway and load it in Eclipse. Than copy the classpath settings and \"maven dependencies\" to your own project.<\/p>\n\n<p>If you figure out where you went wrong, maybe post it here, so others can benefit.<\/p>\n",
